                "name": "Web Programming", "avg_duration": "50-60", "sales_pitch": "", "description": "A good website should be responsive, dynamic, interactive and well-designed. In order to create a good website web developers must be experienced in a number of coding languages. \r\n\r\nBy studying the Alison Learning Path in Web Programming you will learn how to use code to create a website. You will learn about different languages you can use to add different functions to your website and style it in different ways.\r\n\r\nThe Alison Learning Path in Web Programming is a series of courses that will cover HTML, CSS3, Javascript and jQuery. These courses will guide you in the development of your website. These courses will allow you to create a website with a wide range of options for functionality and design to suit your needs and to appeal to visitors of the website.", "learning_paths_type": "progress", "courses": ["Web Page Design Using HTML5 and CSS3", "Web Development - Advanced CSS3 Selectors and HTML5 Elements", "JavaScript - Working with the Document Object Model and jQuery Plugins", "JavaScript and jQuery"]
