                "name": "Nursing - Clinical Skills", "avg_duration": "50-60", "sales_pitch": "", "description": "The role of a modern nursing professional is varied and multi-dimensional.  In order to perform the role well a nurse must have a wide range of clinical skills. Clinical skills allow a nurse to monitor and care for their patients correctly so they get the best care and any problems are spotted early.\r\n\r\nThe Alison Learning Path Nursing \u2013 Clinical Skills will present you with an overview of different clinical skills a nurse may require when treating patients. You will learn how nurses use these clinical skills to make sure patients get the best care possible.\r\n\r\nThe Alison Learning Path Nursing \u2013 Clinical Skills is a series of courses that will introduce you to some of the many clinical skills nursing professionals possess, giving you an overview of good nursing practices and techniques in different situations.", "learning_paths_type": "progress", "courses": ["Nursing Studies - Clinical Skills: Caring for Cardiovascular Patients", "Nursing Studies - Clinical Skills: Caring for Respiratory Patients", "Nursing Studies - Clinical Skills: The Digestive System", "Nursing Studies - Clinical Skills: Neurological Disorders"]
